<HEADLINE>
<P>
PURSE-SNATCHING SUSPECT ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego police have arrested a man suspected of attempting to rob a 77-year 
old Rancho Bernardo woman in a shopping center parking lot earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
Felipe Vallejo-Carachure 18, of the 2800 block of K Street was arrested 
Wednesday after he came voluntarily into the northeast area station for 
questioning, Lt. Richard Bennett said. 
</P>
<P>
A second suspect is being sought in the attempted robbery, which occurred in 
the parking lot of Bernardo Plaza on Dec. 15. 
</P>
<P>
Bertha Ridderhof of Rancho Bernardo was returning to her car about 9 p.m. As 
she placed a package on the roof of her car, a man grabbed her purse. She held 
onto the purse and was dragged to the ground. Onlookers saw the struggle and 
came to her aid, Bennett said. 
</P>
<P>
Ridderhof sustained facial and head injuries and was taken to Sharp Memorial 
Hospital where she was treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
The assailant escaped in a car driven by another man, who police are still 
seeking, Bennett said. 
</P>
