<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TOMKO SCORES 55 POINTS IN EL DORADO'S VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brett Tomko scored 55 points, the third-highest total in Orange County history, 
in El Dorado High School's 86-83 overtime victory against Compton in a 
consolation game of the Brea-Olinda Tournament Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Tomko, a 6-foot-4 senior forward who had never scored more than 24 points in a 
game and had a 17.2 average, scored 23 points in the fourth quarter to help El 
Dorado (5-5) rally from a 60-45 deficit. Tomko added seven points in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
Tomko's performance tied Mark Wulfemeyer, who scored 55 for Troy in 1974. 
Loara's Tes Whitlock scored 68 points Saturday to break the 80-year-old record 
of 58, set by Art Worthy of Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Tomko, who made 20 of 26 shots from the field and 15 of 17 free throws, broke 
the school record of 42 set in 1980 by Ken Botka. 
</P>
<P>
"Most of his shots were from inside the key," El Dorado Coach Wayne Carlson 
said. "They never shut him down at all. We just kept getting the ball to him." 
</P>
<P>
In the Coast Christmas tournament at Estancia High School: 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 67, Dana Hills 50 -- Son Ly had 24 points and Matt Fuerbringer 21 for 
Estancia in a second-round game. 
</P>
<P>
Edison 53, Irvine 45 -- Greg Miller had 14 points and Brandon Jessie 12 for 
Edison in a second-round game. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 71, Huntington Beach 65 -- David Beilstein had 19 points and Thomas 
Clayton 18 for Tustin, the county's top-ranked team, in a second-round game. 
Bryan Chang scored 24 points, including five three-pointers, for Huntington 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 57, Laguna Hills 46 -- Jon Upham had 20 points as the Sea Kings 
outscored the Hawks, 32-22, in the second half of a second-round consolation 
game. Paul LaMott had 22 points for Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia JV 49, Mission Viejo 44 -- Russell King scored 13 points as Estancia 
outscored Mission Viejo, 26-20, in the second half of a second-round 
consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
In the Burger King Prepstar Shootout: 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 72, Seneca (S.C.) 64 -- El Toro trailed by two at the half and fell 
behind, 41-32, early in the third quarter before rallying in the first round at 
the Cumberland County Civic Center in Fayetteville, N.C. The Chargers (7-4) 
led, 53-48, after three quarters and were never challenged thereafter. Rob 
Johnson had 25 points, seven rebounds and six assists and Jeremy Hogue added 22 
points for El Toro. The Chargers will play the tournament's second-seeded team, 
Rice High School of New York, at 3:30 p.m. (PST) today in the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
