<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The largest U.S. amphibious task force to leave the Pacific Coast in 25 years 
arrived in the Philippines on Thursday on its way to bolster allied forces in 
the Persian Gulf, the U.S. 7th Fleet said. 
</P>
<P>
A 7th Fleet announcement said the armada of 13 combat ships staged simulated 
amphibious assaults before arriving at Subic Bay Naval Base, 50 miles northwest 
of Manila. 
