<P>
SIX TROJANS TO PLAY IN ALL-STAR GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six USC seniors will play in postseason all-star games: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Linebacker Scott Ross, offensive tackle Pat Harlow and offensive guard Mark 
Tucker will play in the Hula Bowl Jan. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 -- On the same day, flanker Gary Wellman will play in the Senior Bowl at 
Mobile, Ala. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Harlow, tailback Ricky Ervins and defensive guard Don Gibson will play in 
the Japan Bowl Jan. 13 at Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Gibson and Ross will play in the East-West Shrine game Jan. 26 at Stanford. 
</P>
<P>
Coach Larry Smith said USC has received unwritten commitments from 12 recruits, 
about twice the number that would usually have committed by this time. Letters 
of intent can't be signed until Feb. 6. "We've really gotten off to a great 
start," said Smith, who hopes to sign 24 players. "We had about 30 guys visit 
and we've gotten 12 commitments. We've got another 35 visiting after the first 
of the year." 
</P>
<P>
Among those who have committed is Smith's son, Corby, a quarterback who led 
Loyola High to the Southern Section Division I championship. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
