<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VALLEY WINS 9TH IN ROW, 84-67, WITH FLURRY OF 3-POINT BASKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tisa Rush scored 23 points and four other players scored in double figures to 
pace Valley College to an 84-67 victory over El Camino on Thursday in the first 
round of the Fullerton tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs (14-1), who have won nine consecutive games since losing to 
Moorpark, were ranked No. 1 in the state in the latest J.C. Athletic Bureau 
rankings. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs made nine three-point baskets, erasing the school record of seven 
set in 1986-87. Rush and Sylvia Castaneda each had three. Castaneda scored 15 
points and Katina Mines, Roz Linton and Wendy Bruse each finished with 12 for 
the Monarchs. 
</P>
<P>
In another first-round Fullerton tournament game: 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 91, Long Beach City 69 -- Shannon Solway had 24 points and 10 rebounds 
to lead the Cougars. Guards Keira Irwin (six assists) and Shawnee Danels 
(seven) had little trouble breaking Long Beach's full-court press. 
</P>
<P>
MEN 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 99, Cerritos 86 -- J. R. Rider scored 36 points and teammate 
Tony Madison added 30, including six three-point baskets, to lead the Marauders 
(10-3) past Cerritos (15-5) in a first-round game of the College of the Desert 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley led, 49-41, at halftime and never trailed. Rider pulled down 13 
rebounds for the Marauders and teammate Ennis Wesley scored 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 98, Bellevue (Wash.) 80 -- Reggie Bell scored 27 points and had 13 
rebounds to lead Canyons (7-7) to the first-round win at the Canyons 
tournament. 
</P>
