<HEADLINE>
<P>
HART TOURNAMENT; 
</P>
<P>
SAUGUS CONTINUES ROLL WITH DECISIVE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saugus High Coach John Clark remembers Dec. 10 well -- the day of a seven-point 
loss to Rio Mesa in the first round of the Beverly Hills tournament. 
</P>
<P>
"We played absolutely terrible," Clark said. "We shot poorly and were selfish. 
I lectured their butt off for about 35 minutes. I challenged them to put it on 
the line." 
</P>
<P>
Saugus rose to the occasion Thursday night in a 74-33 victory over San Fernando 
in a championship quarterfinal of the Hart tournament to notch its fourth win 
in a row since a loss to Ventura in the consolation final of the Beverly Hills 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Centurions (9-3) have scored 261 points in the past four games, an average 
of 65.3 points, while limiting opponents to 123 points (30.8). 
</P>
<P>
Saugus center Greg Yumbar scored a career-high 28 points and pulled down 12 
rebounds. Geoff Dains and Steve Tampus added 13 and 12 points. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus, which raced to a 22-4 advantage in the first quarter against Cabrillo 
in the first round Wednesday, built a 12-0 lead against San Fernando (4-7) with 
Jeromy Smith, who recorded five steals in the contest, scoring six of the 
Centurions' first eight points. 
</P>
<P>
Ruben Caballero scored the Tigers' first points with 3 minutes 48 seconds left 
in the period. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus defeated San Fernando, 77-55, earlier in the season in the Saugus 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
"We always try to pressure on defense," said Yumbar, a 6-foot-5 senior. "We 
have to hustle because our team isn't that big." 
</P>
<P>
Saugus led, 17-11, after the first period, but limited San Fernando to three 
points in the first six minutes of the second quarter and expanded its lead to 
36-14 with 2:21 left before halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Yumbar, who connected on 12 of 16 from the field, was five of five during the 
second-quarter run. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus made 27 of 53 from the field (50.9%) in the game and limited San 
Fernando to seven, nine and six points in the final three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
"We shot about as well as we could," Clark said. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando did not score the final 2:12 after trailing, 63-33. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Riggio and Chris Hernandez each had six assists for Saugus, which will 
play Hart in the semifinals tonight at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
In other championship quarterfinal games: 
</P>
<P>
Hart 87, Calabasas 62 -- Hart scored 18 consecutive points in the third quarter 
to increase a 25-24 lead. Ali Peek, who was eight of 12 from the field, scored 
seven of his 19 points during the run. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Halcovich scored a game-high 20 points and Marty Downen added 17 for Hart 
(7-5). Peek and Downen each grabbed 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Young led Calabasas (4-6) with 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 64, Westlake 57 -- Brock Chase led Antelope Valley with 22 
points and John Van Spyk had 22 for Westlake. 
</P>
<P>
East Bakersfield 79, Glendale 71 -- Mike Wright and Hai Tran scored 15 and 14 
points for Glendale (6-5). East Bakersfield will meet Antelope Valley tonight 
at 6 in the other semifinal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
