<P>
Hong Kong Millionaires Advised on Immigration: The U.S. Consulate began 
advising impatient Hong Kong millionaires on how to get in line for immigrant 
visas to the United States in return for $1-million investments in U.S. 
ventures. Under immigration law effective last month, visas will be granted to 
aliens able to invest at least $1 million in a venture that employs 10 or more 
Americans. Similar laws in Canada, Australia and Britain have caused tens of 
thousands of Hong Kong Chinese to seek immigration papers. 
