<P>
Benzene Found in Denture Adhesives: New York's consumer watchdog and the 
federal government warned that testing showed three brands of dental adhesive 
with high levels of the chemical benzene, a known carcinogen. 
</P>
<P>
The Food and Drug Administration identified the brands as Orafix Special, Brace 
and, to a lesser degree, Cushion Grip. All three are being recalled by their 
manufacturers. Officials said there was no immediate health hazard but that it 
could pose a danger over many years. 
</P>
