<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO, LAGUNA NIGUEL; 
</P>
<P>
DRIVERS TO ENCOUNTER 2 SOBRIETY CHECKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies will set up a sobriety checkpoint tonight at an undisclosed 
location in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
On Saturday night, deputies will set up a checkpoint in Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
Both stops will operate between 10 p.m. and 2 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
"We stay busy most of the night, but we tend to see a lot of people right at 10 
p.m., mostly coming home from malls," said Lt. George Johnson. "Then there's a 
second rush of people coming from the bars at around 1:30 a.m." 
</P>
<P>
Over the holidays, the department has scheduled eight sobriety checkpoints in 
four South County cities -- Mission Viejo, Dana Point, Laguna Niguel and San 
Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
At their first checkpoint in early December, deputies stopped about 1,400 
vehicles and arrested nine people on suspicion of drunk driving. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
