<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY 1990-1991 RESOLUTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
" I have made up my mind that the 1990s is my decade to retire from education. 
I think I have been a highly intense person in terms of my career, and I have 
been reflecting on that and working on bringing a balance in my life with a 
mixture of hard work and also taking time out for myself. 
</P>
<P>
I think that as a nation we have hit rock bottom in terms of supporting our 
schools. But I'm not discouraged because I feel we have the attention of the 
leadership -- on the federal, state and local levels -- and that's what it's 
going to take. Either as an active public school administrator and/or as a 
private consultant, I will dedicate the remainder of my life to young people. 
I'm going to speak up and say, "If you want quality (education), you'll have to 
pay for it." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Cynthia Grennan, superintendent, Anaheim Union High School District. 
