<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVITE FALLS TO INGLEWOOD IN FINAL SECONDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Bowman's 13-foot jump shot with 18 seconds remaining helped Inglewood 
High School to a 62-59 upset over Servite in the first round of the Katella 
Klassic Thursday night at Katella High School. 
</P>
<P>
Servite's Adam Anderson put the Friars ahead, 59-58, with 40 seconds to play 
after he rebounded a Friar miss and scored on a five-foot bank shot for the 
last of his 17 points. 
</P>
<P>
After Bowman (22 points) connected to give the Sentinels (7-6) a 60-59 lead, 
Servite's last chance went awry when Inglewood's Codi Evans (20 points) stole 
the ball from Eddie Rubio and made two free throws with three seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Servite (8-3) made 20 of 29 shots (69 percent) in the first three quarters, but 
went cold in the final period, making four of 14 attempts (29 percent). MICHAEL 
ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122890-0146 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 328482 </DOCID>
