<P>
SCHOOL WINS AT BASKETBALL -- ON 75TH TRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CARMICHAELS, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jefferson-Morgan High School ended a 74-game, 3 1/2-season losing streak in 
basketball Thursday night by upsetting Mapletown 71 to 69 in a holiday 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
A wrestling power whose success hasn't extended to basketball, Jefferson-Morgan 
won on the court for the first time since Feb. 3, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad for the kids more than anything else," Jefferson-Morgan Coach Jim 
Romanus said. "It was tough for them to keep playing when all they kept hearing 
about was this streak." 
</P>
<P>
Romanus, who coached the Rockets through the entire slump, added: "It's hard to 
believe. Sometimes I think it's a dream and I'm going to wake up." 
</P>
<P>
Mapletown entered the game with a 5-2 record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
