<HEADLINE>
<P>
CZECHS ADVANCE IN TENNIS CUP, FACE U.S. NEXT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PERTH, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Petr Korda beat Carl-Uwe Steeb in singles and teamed with Regina Rajchrtova for 
a doubles victory today as Czechoslovakia defeated Germany, 2-1, to advance to 
the quarterfinals of the Hopman Cup. 
</P>
<P>
Isabel Cueto beat Rajchrtova, 2-6, 6-2, 6-4, to give Germany a 1-0 lead, but 
Korda defeated Steeb, 6-3, 2-6, 6-2, and combined with Rachjrtova to beat Steeb 
and Cueto, 6-1, 6-3, in mixed doubles. 
</P>
<P>
Cueto was too steady for the error-prone Rajchrtova in the opening singles, but 
Korda then out-served and out-volleyed Steeb in a hard-fought match. 
</P>
<P>
Steeb played despite the death of his father earlier in the week. 
</P>
<P>
Czechoslovakia, the seventh seed in the 12-nation exhibition tournament, will 
play the top-seeded United States in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
The American pair of David Wheaton and Zina Garrison had a first-round bye, 
along with defending champion Spain, Switzerland and the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
France, with a 2-0 victory over the Netherlands, also advanced to the 
quarterfinals, where it will face defending champion Spain. Catherine Tanvier 
beat Manon Bollegraf, 6-3, 6-4, and Guy Forget defeated Michiel Schapers, 6-4, 
6-4. 
</P>
<P>
In the remaining first-round match, Yugoslavia was scheduled to play Italy with 
the winner advancing to the quarterfinals against the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
Switzerland will play Australia in the other quarterfinal match. 
</P>
<P>
Each match consists of men's singles, women's singles and mixed doubles 
matches. 
</P>
<P>
The exhibition tournament at the Burswood Superdome continues through Jan. 3 
and is the first of a series of warmup events for the Australian Open, which 
begins Jan. 14 at the National Tennis Center in Melbourne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
